-- Scotiabank to buy rest of DundeeWealth for C$2.3 billion
-- 
-- Mon Nov 22, 2010 10:30am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/11/22/us-scotia-dundee-idUSTRE6AL34S20101122

 

 TORONTO  (Reuters) - Bank of Nova Scotia, Canada's third-largest lender, said on Monday it agreed to acquire the 82 percent of independent wealth management groupDundeeWealth it does not already own for C$2.3 billion. 

 The deal is designed to build out the bank's wealth management capabilities and values DundeeWealth at C$21 a share, or C$3.2 billion. "The acquisition of DundeeWealth demonstrates our strong commitment to build our wealth management presence in Canada and aligns to our global wealth management strategy," said Rick Waugh, Scotiabank President and CEO. Scotiabank said it will offer 0.2497 of a Scotiabank common share and, at the election of each shareholder, either C$5.00 in cash or 0.2 of a C$25.00, 3.70 percent five-year rate reset Scotiabank preferred share for each DundeeWealth common share, including common shares issuable on conversion of other shares. Scotiabank's shares were down 0.6 percent at C$54.31 in early Toronto trading, while Dundee's stock was halted. (Reporting by  Pav Jordan )